10.1 Moat Components
10.2 Competitive Differentiation
10.3 The Compounding Advantage
Over time, the advantage compounds:
Time 0: Business Context = Basic | Recommendations = Generic | Switching Cost = Low
Time 6 Months: Business Context = Rich | Recommendations = Targeted | Switching Cost =
Medium
Time 18 Months: Business Context = Deep | Recommendations = Precisely Tuned | Switching Cost
= High
A competitor cannot replicate 18 months of accumulated business intelligence and monthly CDT
training cycles.
11. Business Model & Viability
11.1 Revenue Streams
11.2 Unit Economics
11.3 Scalability Path
Phase 1 — Agency Model (Now): Refleqt internal team produces. Limited capacity. High-touch,
high-margin. Goal: Validate demand, refine quality.
Phase 2 — Creator Marketplace (6-12 months): Open creator onboarding. Anonymized execution.
Performance-based reputation. Goal: Scale supply, maintain quality.
Phase 3 — Full Marketplace (12-24 months): Premium creator bidding. Microcontracts. Self-serve
tiers. Goal: Network effects, market leadership.
12. Summary: The Refleqt Thesis
12.1 What We're Building
A context-aware marketing artifact marketplace that:
Learns your business through persistent, evolving intelligence + monthly CDT training
Plugs into your ecosystem without requiring continuous API integration
Generates strategy via per-customer AI that evolves its beliefs monthly
Delivers quality through human creators with performance-tracked reputations
Maintains control with customer-owned calendars, deployment, and data
Proves results via real-time, attributed performance dashboards
12.2 Why Now
AI capability: LLMs can now generate sophisticated strategy, not just content
Fine-tuning accessibility: Per-customer model training is now economically viable
Creator economy maturity: Distributed workforce ready for new platforms
Marketing fragmentation: Businesses overwhelmed by channels, need orchestration
Attribution technology: Finally possible to close the loop on content ROI
12.3 The Bet
"The businesses that win in the next decade will have persistent intelligence about themselves —
and the marketing systems that leverage it. Refleqt is that system."
